<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Dengue/DHF - Philippines 980902230329
Dengue/DHF - Philippines (02) 980909075200
Dengue/DHF - Philippines (03) 980918002843
Dengue/DHF - Philippines (04) 980924083221
Source: Manila Standard Fri 25 Sep 1998
By Dulce Arguelles, Jude O. Marfil & Rendy Isip [edited
Via: GPHIN 28 Sep 1998

Latest count
-------------
The latest dengue count showed a nationwide total of 15 650 cases with
276 deaths. The National Capital Region (NCR) has the largest share of
cases at 3144.
Dengue hot spots have been reduced to two, Bagong Silang in Caloocan
City and Bacoor in Cavite. The towns of San Antonio and Jaen in Nueva
Ecija and Dumaguete City, Negros Oriental are still in the grip of a
dengue outbreak.
Meanwhile, the Department of Health [DoH warned that dengue cases were
expected to hit a record of 72 000 this year. Dr. Eric Tayag, head of
the department of epidemiology of San Lazaro Hospital, warned that
unless bold preventive actions were [taken, at least 2 percent of
dengue patients will die of the disease.
In San Fernando, Pampanga, the DoH said dengue has already claimed 34
deaths as cases in Central Luzon have risen to 1933 since last January.
Lenny Carreon, information officer of DoH said that based on the records
of the department since 19 Sep1998, at least 686 cases of dengue
occurred in Nueva Ecija with 13 deaths, in Bataan with 109 cases,
Bulacan with 426 cases, in Pampanga with 310 cases, Tarlac with 251
cases and in Zambales with 153 cases.
